# What i did:
I used the parsing module (data_extraction_M1.py) in this assignment. The objective was to read respondent answer files and cut the chosen answers into a list of structerd list of integers.
# How it works:
The extract answers sequence reads each line of the file and recognize blocks of questions. There are four possible answers in each question and the answer that is chosen is indicated by [x]. The function records the position of the selected answer(1-4), or 0 if unanswered. The write_answers_sequence function then saves the extracted data into a text file for further analysis.
  # Challenges:
  One of the difficulties was to make sure that the functionality properly addresses the unanswered questions. Inconsistencies in file formatting, including additional spaces or unforessen lines were another issues.
  # Evidence / testing
I ran the code on sample files like a1.txt, and confirmed that the list of output contained 100 values. I also ensured that the output file is generated in the output folder.
